						<div align="justify">
							So much has been going that this is going to be a huge update.<br><br>The past couple of days i have been working on a program to help with the web page. Its finally done now! Updating the news will be alot simpler and i can control the colors alot easier.<br><Br>Speaking of colors what does everyone think of this color scheme for the main page? Any suggestions or comments about it? I plan on keeping the format the way it is with the statue in the background. I just want to tweak the colors really. Although if you make a really good argument i can change it. Im just really attached to that statue.<br><Br>If you take a look at the <a href="/~mboutin/CrimsonDragons/member.html">members</a> page you will see that is has been updated and alot of people have been moved around. The reason for this is there seems to be alot of people who i don't see very often. I removed them from active houses and put them in the non active one. Once you start playing that character again please give me a ring and ill move you into an active house.<br><Br>Recently a few people have left guild, and ill talk about that more later. So because of the low membership i want to recruit a few more people. Preferably in the mid teens to mid 20s. If you group with someone who you think would be a great addition into the guild. Try to group with them a few times at least then invite them.<br><br>Now the news you have all been waiting for! I think I have decided what I shall do about the House Leader situation, with great help from Aeleric. As you can see Anyrael has been removed from the the guild. I talked to him last night and his RL is getting busy so he has very little time for EQ. Now we have a Taskmaster and two House Leader positions open. Haggin, Galeof, Orbit have been nominated so far. If you have any more nominations please tell me. I would like each nominee to write a short speech telling what you will do, how much free beer you will give away, etc... After that has been done i plan on asking everyone for their vote starting next weekend. The first vote will be for Taskmaster, then House Leader 2 then House leader 3. Good luck to you all and get thos speaches ready.<br><Br>I seemed to have neglected the <a href="/~mboutin/CrimsonDragons/TradeSkills.html">Trade Skills</a> page for a while. So if you have any info or a desire to become an official guild trade skill master just speak up.<br><BR>It seems we have all come to the conclusion that the new message board stinks! If you can find a better one PLEASE tell me so i can get it set up for us. Until then we must bear with it.<br><Br>I have need of some HTML help. Please goto this <a href="/~mboutin/CrimsonDragons/Test.html">page</a>. You should notice the IRPA icon in the top right. Does anyone know how to get rid of the yellow border?<br><br>Sometime later today you should see a new link on the left sidebar. From now on im going to have a weekly riddle. The first person to solve it will get some prize. Each week after the previous riddle has been solved a new one will go up. Here is this weeks riddle:<br><center><b>A Bent Riddle</b><br>Rain is spent<br>Now colors bent<br>Frame a clear, blue sky</center><br>Good luck on this one, It shouldn't be too hard.
